  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "Attending a TED Talk can vary in cost depending on the event. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **TED Conferences**: The flagship TED Conference, held annually in Vancouver, Canada, is quite expensive, with tickets typically costing around $10,000 USD or more. This includes access to all sessions, meals, and networking events.\n\n2. **TEDGlobal and TEDSummit**: These international conferences also have high ticket prices, often in the range of $6,000 to $8,000 USD.\n\n3. **TEDx Events**: TEDx events are independently organized and can vary widely in price. Some are free, while others may charge anywhere from $50 to $500 USD, depending on the location, speakers, and event scale.\n\n4. **Online Access**: Many TED Talks are available for free on the TED website or YouTube. Additionally, TED offers live streaming of some events, sometimes for a fee.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date pricing, it\u2019s best to check the official TED or TEDx event websites.",
